---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import EmailForm from '../../components/EmailForm.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="The Ways of the World — Ironwood Books"
  description="A father's guide to life's essential wisdom — the things schools never taught you about how the world actually works. Free ebook download."
>

  <article class="book-page">

    <section class="book-header">
      <div class="container book-header-inner">
        <div class="book-cover">
          <img
            src="/images/the-ways-of-the-world-cover.jpg"
            alt="The Ways of the World — book cover"
            class="cover-img"
            width="600"
            height="990"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="book-info">
          <div class="book-tags">
            <span class="tag tag-ages">Ages 14+</span>
            <span class="tag tag-topic">Life Philosophy</span>
            <span class="tag tag-type">Nonfiction</span>
          </div>
          <h1>The Ways of the World</h1>
          <p class="book-byline">A Father's Guide to Life's Essential Wisdom</p>
          <p class="book-description">
            Here is something worth knowing about school: it was not designed for you. It was designed in 18th-century Prussia by Frederick the Great, who needed soldiers and factory workers — people who could follow orders and not ask too many questions.
          </p>
          <p class="book-description">
            What it never taught you — what it was never designed to teach you — is how the world actually works. Why power accumulates where it does. Why money flows the way it does. Why some ideas survive for thousands of years and others die in a generation. These are not secrets. They are patterns. And once you can see them, you see them everywhere.
          </p>
          <p class="book-description">
            This book is one father's attempt to pass those patterns on.
          </p>
          <div class="book-actions">
            <a href="#download" class="btn btn-primary">Get Free Ebook</a>
            <a href="https://www.amazon.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline">Buy Paperback on Amazon</a>
          </div>
          <div class="book-meta-list">
            <div><span>Length</span><strong>~35,000 words</strong></div>
            <div><span>Reading level</span><strong>Ages 14 and up</strong></div>
            <div><span>Format</span><strong>Nonfiction / Philosophy</strong></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="book-about">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="about-inner">
          <div class="about-copy">
            <span class="section-label">What This Book Is</span>
            <h2>A map, not a manual</h2>
            <p>
              The father who wrote this didn't know everything. He knew what he'd observed — in business, in history, in his own failures and recoveries. He filtered it through the thinkers he trusted most: Marcus Aurelius, Aristotle, Dostoevsky, Nietzsche, Naval Ravikant.
            </p>
            <p>
              Then he wrote it down for his son, clearly, without hedging, in case he wasn't around to say it in person.
            </p>
            <p>
              A map is not the territory. It leaves things out and it simplifies. But a good map is worth more than no map at all — especially when you're trying to find your way through unfamiliar terrain and everyone around you is pretending they already know the route.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="about-toc">
            <h3>What's inside</h3>
            <ul class="toc-list">
              {[
                { part: "Part One", title: "How to See the World", desc: "Entropy, evolution, systems thinking, and the lenses that make everything else visible." },
                { part: "Part Two", title: "How the World Actually Works", desc: "Power, money, incentives, institutions, and why they behave the way they do." },
                { part: "Part Three", title: "How to Build a Life", desc: "Work, relationships, identity, and the decisions that compound over time." },
                { part: "Part Four", title: "Advice", desc: "Direct. Unhedged. What a father actually wants his son to know." },
              ].map(s => (
                <li class="toc-item">
                  <span class="toc-part">{s.part}</span>
                  <strong>{s.title}</strong>
                  <p>{s.desc}</p>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="book-voices">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="section-label">The Influences</span>
        <h2>Written through the lens of people worth reading</h2>
        <div class="voices-grid">
          {[
            { name: "Marcus Aurelius", note: "The Meditations — clarity, discipline, and the daily practice of keeping judgment clean." },
            { name: "Aristotle", note: "Excellence is a habit, not an act. The idea that character is built through repeated choices." },
            { name: "Lao Tzu", note: "The Tao Te Ching — softness overcomes hardness. The power of knowing when not to act." },
            { name: "Sun Tzu", note: "The Art of War — understanding leverage, terrain, and the conflict before the conflict begins." },
            { name: "Nietzsche", note: "Will to power. The creation of values. The danger of living by someone else's code." },
            { name: "Naval Ravikant", note: "Specific knowledge, leverage, and the compounding nature of accountability and reputation." },
            { name: "Balaji Srinivasan", note: "Network states and the next phase of civilization. Technology as the force that rewrites power." },
            { name: "Dostoevsky", note: "The Brothers Karamazov — suffering, faith, and what it means to bear the weight of being human." },
            { name: "Kurt Vonnegut", note: "So it goes. The dark humor that makes difficult truths livable without looking away." },
            { name: "George Orwell", note: "Language is power. Clarity of expression is clarity of thought — and clarity of thought is freedom." },
            { name: "Plato", note: "The Republic — justice, the examined life, and the idea that most people live in a cave of their own making." },
            { name: "Machiavelli", note: "The Prince — power without sentiment. How the world actually works when the idealists aren't in the room." },
          ].map(v => (
            <div class="voice-card">
              <strong>{v.name}</strong>
              <p>{v.note}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="book-download" id="download">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="download-box">
          <div class="download-copy">
            <span class="section-label">Free Ebook</span>
            <h2>Read it free. Keep it forever.</h2>
            <p>
              Enter your email and we'll send you the full book as a PDF.
              If you want it on a shelf, the paperback is on Amazon.
            </p>
            <ul class="download-perks">
              <li>Full book in PDF — no signup fee, no catch</li>
              <li>Yours to keep and read at any time</li>
              <li>No spam, ever — unsubscribe any time</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="download-form">
            <EmailForm
              heading="Get the free ebook"
              subtext="Enter your email and we'll send it straight to your inbox."
              variant="stacked"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="book-excerpt">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="section-label">From the Introduction</span>
        <blockquote>
          <p>"The day I found out your mother was pregnant, I had two kinds of thoughts in quick succession. The first kind was logistics... The second kind of thought was harder to name. It sounded like: <em>What do I actually know? What do I wish someone had told me? And if something were to happen to me before I could tell him — what would he be missing?</em>"</p>
          <p>"That second kind of thought is why this book exists."</p>
          <footer>— From the Introduction</footer>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>

</MainLayout>

<style>
  .book-header { background: var(--cream); padding: 4rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .book-header-inner { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: start; }

  .cover-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 0 16px 48px rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
    display: block;
  }

  .book-tags { display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .tag { font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 0.2rem 0.55rem; border-radius: 3px; }
  .tag-ages { background: var(--green-light); color: var(--green); }
  .tag-topic { background: var(--bronze-light); color: var(--bronze); }
  .tag-type { background: var(--border); color: var(--ink-mid); }

  .book-info h1 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.6rem); margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .book-byline { color: var(--ink-light); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; font-style: italic; }
  .book-description { color: var(--ink-mid); margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; }
  .book-actions { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 1.75rem 0; }
  .book-meta-list { display: flex; gap: 2rem; flex-wrap: wrap; padding-top: 1.25rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .book-meta-list div { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.2rem; }
  .book-meta-list span { font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--ink-light); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  .book-meta-list strong { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--ink); }

  .book-about { background: var(--white); padding: var(--section-pad); }
  .about-inner { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: start; }
  .about-copy h2 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .about-copy p { color: var(--ink-mid); margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; }
  .about-toc h3 { font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--ink-light); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .toc-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; }
  .toc-item { border-left: 3px solid var(--green); padding-left: 1rem; }
  .toc-part { font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--bronze); display: block; margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }
  .toc-item strong { font-size: 0.95rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.2rem; color: var(--ink); }
  .toc-item p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--ink-light); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0; }

  .book-voices { background: var(--cream); padding: var(--section-pad); }
  .book-voices h2 { font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 1.9rem); margin-bottom: 2rem; max-width: 600px; }
  .voices-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 1.25rem; }
  .voice-card { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.25rem; }
  .voice-card strong { display: block; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--green); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .voice-card p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--ink-light); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }

  .book-download { background: var(--green-light); padding: var(--section-pad); }
  .download-box { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: center; background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 3rem; }
  .download-copy h2 { font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .download-copy p { color: var(--ink-mid); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .download-perks { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .download-perks li { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--ink-mid); padding-left: 1.25rem; position: relative; }
  .download-perks li::before { content: "✓"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--green); font-weight: 700; }

  .book-excerpt { background: var(--green); padding: var(--section-pad); }
  .book-excerpt .section-label { color: rgba(235,241,236,0.65); }
  blockquote { max-width: 700px; border-left: 3px solid var(--bronze); padding-left: 2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  blockquote p { color: rgba(245,240,232,0.9); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-style: italic; }
  blockquote p:last-of-type { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  blockquote footer { font-size: 0.82rem; color: rgba(245,240,232,0.55); }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .book-header-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cover-art { max-width: 240px; aspect-ratio: 2/3; }
    .about-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .download-box { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding: 2rem; gap: 2rem; }
  }
</style>
